President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key roles within the government. Senator Evan Bayh will be appointed as a member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board. Bayh has previously served on committees such as the Senate Armed Services Committee and Senate Intelligence Committee. Donna Brazile will be appointed as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. She is a former interim Chair of the Democratic National Committee and has lectured at numerous colleges and universities. Ambassador James Costos will also be appointed as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. He is a former U.S. Ambassador to Spain and Andorra and is currently involved in various cultural and business organizations. Lastly, Stephen Schneck will be appointed as a Commissioner of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom. He is a political philosopher and has been involved in organizations advocating for environmental justice and restorative justice.